#Word Frequency Counter
Given a file article.txt,
Count frequency of each word (ignore case and punctuation)

Algorithm :- Open article.txt in read mode
              Read full content of file
              Convert text to lowercase (ignore case)
              Remove punctuation (.,!? etc.)
              Split text into words
              Create empty dictionary for frequency
              For each word:
                        If word exists → increment count
                        Else → add with count = 1
                        Display word frequencies

#Code:-
import string   # for punctuation removal

# open file
with open("article.txt", "r") as file:
    text = file.read()

# convert to lowercase (ignore case)
text = text.lower()

# remove punctuation
for ch in string.punctuation:
    text = text.replace(ch, "")

# split into words
words = text.split()

# dictionary to store frequency
freq = {}

# counting frequency
for word in words:
    if word in freq:
        freq[word] += 1   # increase count
    else:
        freq[word] = 1    # first time

# display result
for word, count in freq.items():
    print(word, ":", count)
